<br>
Thorbadin....<br>
There is an actual hate list and a modified hate list. The mob decides who to attack based on the modified hate list. Taunt will take you to the top of the actual hate list, but it does not directly affect the modified hate list.<br>
<br>
Some modifiers are distance, sitting/standing, low health. If a person is below 2 bubs of health a successful taunt will not get that mob back onto you until that person dies or is healed. Distance modification of the hatelist is why rangers can do crazy damage with bows and not gain aggro. They are generally far enough away to counteract the high aggro from their damage. You can also see it by sitting. If you have a fair amount of hate to start with, you can sit and see a mob come running immediately. If you stand up before it gets to you, it turns back to attack the person who was tanking it originally. If a mob is snared, you can actually keep it from hitting anyone by doing this. <br>
<br>
These things will have a different effect on different mobs. Undead and boss mobs generally have a much higher modifier for distance, i.e. they are much more inclined to attack the closest person. Most non undead xp mobs aren't nearly as sensitive to distance. That distance modifier is why you want to stand as close as possible to the mob you are tanking. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686">Graal MacBladefury</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
