<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Distance modification of the hatelist is why rangers can do crazy damage with bows and not gain aggro. They are generally far enough away to counteract the high aggro from their damage.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Have that ranger do mad damage then have him run up to the mob.  It will completely ignore him.  Ranged attacks generate almost no hate.  In fact I would say damage has little to do with hate.  However, weapons that do a lot of damage do build a lot of hate.    But his is mostly from a built in 'threat' of the weapon.  THus you can have an enchanter with an insane two hander with ZERO skill in 2hb taunting mobs like a crazy mofo with doing no damage.  THe mob registers the 'threat' of that weapon landing and acts accordingly.  This is also why defensive does not hurt taunting abilites.<br>
<br>
Arrows have almost no 'threat' and thus generate almost no agro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vwar>Vwar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/4/03 2:29:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is taunt?</span><hr size=1>  This will be my first post on this site , but mashing is not the way to go,,<br>
