<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Did mob attack you or chanter? Next time taunt 4 times see where he goes.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Say taunt has a 33% chance of working on any given attempt vs. a mob. Taunt it once, 33% chance of a succesful taunt. Taunt it four times, and you have a 1-(1-33%)^4 ~80% chance that one of the taunts were succesful.<br>
<br>
Mashing is bad, does nothing but graying out the button if you have aggro - meaning you can't taunt it off that overaggroing wizard, or the CHealing cleric until it recycles.<br>
